folder: Varick Street & North Moore Street, Manhattan, NY
original_title: Manhattan: Varick Street - North Moore Street
text:
Varick Street, west side, north from North Moore Street, to Eriosson Place (Beach Street), showing under construction an addition to the Merchant's Refrigerating Company. Also seen on the left, are Nos. 27 to 37 North Moore, adjoining and west of the N.W. corner of Varick Streets. These three buildings comprise the original home of the Merchant's Refrigerating Co. The 3-story building on the right, is the 4th Precinct Police Station.

NEG # 334.5

Camera Craft.

January 22, 1925.

original_title: Manhattan: Varick Street - North Moore Street
text:
Varick Street, west side, north from North Moore Street, to Ericsson Place (Beach Street). The tall building has been recently constructed, and is an addition to the Merchant's Refrigerating Co. At the extreme right, is seen the 4th Precinct police Station, at the S.W. corner of Ericsson Place (Beach Street).

January 22, 1925.

Camera Craft.

original_title: Manhattan: North Moore Street - Varick Street
text:
North Moore Street, north side, east from Varick Street, to and including West Broadway. Nos. 1-5 North Moore Street, at, adjoining and north of the N.W. corner of West Broadway, are 3-story frame buildings with brick fronts.

April 3, 1932.

P. L. Sperr.

original_title: Manhattan: Varick Street - North Moore Street
text:
Varick Street, east side, north from North Moore, to Beach Streets. Also shown is North Moore Street, north side, east from Varick Street, to West Broadway. A parking lot occupies the major portion of the east side of Varick Street.

April 2, 1932.

P. L. Sperr.
